Pet Adoption System
• Architecture
The system uses a three-tier architecture: the frontend handles user interaction, the backend processes requests and manages logic, and the database stores all application data.
• Database Model
The database model consists of multiple tables that manage different parts of the system, including users, pets, bookings, reviews, events, and donations. It also includes tables for financial and item donations, as well as features like favorites and notifications to support user interactions and activity tracking.
• Relationships
The system defines relationships between entities where a user can have multiple pets, make many bookings, write several reviews, save favorites, receive notifications, and make both financial and item donations, while each booking links a user with a specific pet.
• Technologies Used
The system uses HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for the frontend, JavaScript for the backend, and MySQL for the database, as these technologies offer a simple, scalable, and efficient solution.
• User Interface
The user interface includes key pages such as login and registration, pet browsing, pet details, and booking, all designed to be simple, user-friendly, and easy to navigate.

